I‚Äôve heard of many cases where people in the meantime have literally gotten over the virus and recovered whilst waiting - only to then be taken away and plonked in a packed facility surrounded by people who are positive - and sometimes sick.

China‚Äôs policy is that all cases of Covid-19 must be taken away to designated centralised quarantine facilities. During this current outbreak in Shanghai there‚Äôs often been a delay meaning people are not being picked up for days or sometimes even a couple of weeks.

I still don‚Äôt understand Shanghai‚Äôs insistence on taking people away to mass quarantine camps days after they‚Äôve tested positive but despite the fact they‚Äôve since gotten over the virus and are testing negative. I‚Äôve heard of two of these cases today alone. It‚Äôs madness.
